This paper deals with the problem of adversarial attacks on deep neural networks, which is a common topic in the sub-fields of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also proposes a new training paradigm to address this problem, which could potentially fall under the sub-field of cryptography and security (cs.CR). Finally, the paper involves training models using a null class, which is a technique that could be relevant to the sub-field of neural networks (cs.NE).
